President Barack Obama announced his intent to nominate several individuals for key administration posts. The nominees include Michael H. Posner for Assistant Secretary of State for Democracy, Human Rights, and Labor; Stephen J. Rapp for Ambassador at Large for War Crimes Issues; Alexander G. Garza for Assistant Secretary for Health Affairs and Chief Medical Officer; Susan L. Kurland for Assistant Secretary for Aviation and International Affairs; Joe Garcia for Director of the Office of Minority Economic Impact; Kenneth A. Spearman for Member of the Board of Directors, Farm Credit Administration; Rolena Adorno for Member of the National Council on the Humanities; and Marvin Krislov for Member of the National Council on the Humanities. These individuals have diverse backgrounds and experiences in their respective fields. President Obama expressed confidence in their abilities to serve the American people and work towards the country's safety and prosperity.